esigns.ca/demo4/download-page/" target="_blank"><strong>Pundit</strong></a></p>\n<p><img title="pundit-thumbnail" height="137" alt="pundit-thumbnail" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/b2-img/2008/06/punditthumbnail.png" width="194" border="0" /> </p>\n<p>Pundit is a three column widget-ready theme designed to focus on the writing. Perfect for news or political blogs or for anyone who anyone who wants to keep it simple.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.wp-magazine.se/free-wordpress-theme-wp-platinum/" target="_blank"><strong>WP Platinum</strong></a></p>\n<p><img title="wp-platinum-thumbnail" height="129" alt="wp-platinum-thumbnail" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/b2-img/2008/06/wpplatinumthumbnail.png" width="200" border="0" /> </p>\n<p>WP Platinum is a 3 column widget-ready theme specifically created for Firefox. The theme has a featured article section.</p>";}i:20;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:54:"Gravatar: Image Transparency, You Want it? You Got it!";s:4:"guid";s:35:"http://gravatar.wordpress.com/?p=55";s:4:"link";s:78:"http://blog.gravatar.com/2008/06/06/image-transparency-you-want-it-you-got-it/";s:11:"description";s:2432:"<div class="snap_preview"><br /><p>After a lot of tinkering, fiddling, poking, and prodding we&#8217;ve revamped the image support in gravatar.  Now if you upload a GIF or a PNG we will preserve any transparency that might be in the image and serve that image to you as a PNG.</p>\n<p>Unfortunately this does not retroactively fix existing images with black instead of transparent backgrounds. You&#8217;ll want to re-upload your transparent images, assign the new image to your email addresses.  After that, give it about 30 minutes and clear your cache. Everything should work and look just fine.</p>\n<p>A note for all you webmasters out there: If you&#8217;re worried about what transparent PNG images look like for your IE visitors, I would recommend taking a look at this handy <a title="Transparent PNGs in Internet Explorer 6" href="http://24ways.org/2007/supersleight-transparent-png-in-ie6">Transparent PNGs in Internet Explorer 6</a> page which offers an explanation, information on workarounds, and a drop-in javascript which will work for all the images on a page.</p>\n<p>Until next time – happy blogging!</p>\n<img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/categories/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/" /> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/tags/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/" /> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=blog.gravatar.com&blog=1886259&post=55&subd=gravatar&ref=&feed=1" /></div>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Fri, 06 Jun 2008 20:18:34 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:11:"apokalyptik";}s:7:"summary";s:2432:"<div class="snap_preview"><br /><p>After a lot of tinkering, fiddling, poking, and prodding we&#8217;ve revamped the image support in gravatar.  Now if you upload a GIF or a PNG we will preserve any transparency that might be in the image and serve that image to you as a PNG.</p>\n<p>Unfortunately this does not retroactively fix existing images with black instead of transparent backgrounds. You&#8217;ll want to re-upload your transparent images, assign the new image to your email addresses.  After that, give it about 30 minutes and clear your cache. Everything should work and look just fine.</p>\n<p>A note for all you webmasters out there: If you&#8217;re worried about what transparent PNG images look like for your IE visitors, I would recommend taking a look at this handy <a title="Transparent PNGs in Internet Explorer 6" href="http://24ways.org/2007/supersleight-transparent-png-in-ie6">Transparent PNGs in Internet Explorer 6</a> page which offers an explanation, information on workarounds, and a drop-in javascript which will work for all the images on a page.</p>\n<p>Until next time – happy blogging!</p>\n<img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/categories/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/" /> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/tags/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/" /> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/gravatar.wordpress.com/55/" /></a> <img al